Explain the role of China's National People Congress to a 5 year old child who lives in London.
<|end|>
<|assistant|>
Hey there! Imagine if you and your friends decided to play a game in your playground, and you all wanted to make sure everyone has fun and plays fair. The National People Congress in China is like that group of friends, but for the whole country called China. They meet once every few years, just like a big meeting, to make rules that help everyone be happy and the country work well together. They talk about what's best for all the people in China and make decisions, like what games to play for the country, just like how you decide what games to play at recess. But remember, they do this for a big family of people, not just one friend!<|end|>